{
  "id": "eekso-garden",
  "name": "Eekso — The Garden (Ambush)",
  "session": "session-26",
  "dmNotes": "SET-PIECE 1 — the flytrap. Structure: LURE → THRESHOLD → CLOSE → FIGHT. The music does the work: start on 'bloom' (genuinely beautiful, zero irony) and hold it longer than feels comfortable. The turn comes from the WORLD first — the plants move, the music follows a beat later.\n\nThreshold = the pool's edge. THE WATER ISN'T REAL — the pool is the thing's STOMACH: clear digestive fluid in a basin of its own flesh. It wraps you up, drags you in, and spines poke you full of holes while the fluid does the slow work. Weak to fire AND slashing (cut the coils). Escape through the sealing archway is a valid win.\n\nLETHALITY (Wes confirmed): the 0-HP-dissolves rule is REAL. No secret safety net — the counterplay is fire, blades, and getting them out in time. (The Revivify scroll in this room's loot insures the REST of the dungeon — it can't help anyone dissolved here: no body, no Revivify.)\n\nSTAT BLOCK: 📖 'The Garden of Eekso' (campaign homebrew, 🏠 in the compendium). CR 7 — under moderate budget on paper, the closing-perimeter mechanics make up the rest, and escape stays viable.",
