  },
  "script": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The Garden"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "cue",
          "kind": "music",
          "ref": "bloom",
          "label": "▶ bloom"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " "
        },
        {
          "type": "cue",
          "kind": "amb",
          "ref": "fap-forest-birds",
          "label": "〜 fap-forest-birds",
          "fadeInMs": 4000
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "You come around the rock and the fortress simply stops being a fortress."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "A garden grows here , walled in old stone, under a hundred feet of black rock.  Flowers in colours that have no business existing this far from the sun. The air is warm. Birds are singing somewhere in the branches."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "After everything behind you, it is the first thing in this place that looks "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "alive",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "italic"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The Wrongnesses"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Only if a player actively looks:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "- "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Perception DC 15:",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "bold"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " the birdsong doesn't move. Same calls, same places, on a loop. - "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Nature DC 15:",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "bold"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " nothing here has ever "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "seeded",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "italic"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " — no saplings, no dead leaves, no litter. This garden has never been young. - "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Investigation DC 17:",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "bold"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " bones at the base of the trees, half-swallowed by root and moss. Not cleaned up — "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "grown over",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "italic"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". - "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Survival DC 13:",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "bold"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " no insect noise. In a garden. None. - "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Nature DC 14 (at the pool):",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "bold"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " no inlet, no outlet, nothing living in it — and touching it, the 'water' is faintly warm, slick, and "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "clings",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "italic"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " for half a second before it lets go."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If they clock it early and back out — "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "let them.",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "bold"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " Escape/avoidance is a valid win."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The Threshold"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "cue",
          "kind": "music",
          "ref": "wrong",
          "label": "▶ wrong"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " "
        },
        {
          "type": "cue",
          "kind": "amb",
          "ref": "fap-cave-creepy",
          "label": "〜 fap-cave-creepy",
          "volume": 0.3,
          "fadeInMs": 5000
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "- "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Trigger:",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "bold"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " approaching the water"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "- The birdsong stops — all of it, at once, mid-phrase"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "- In the silence, every branch in the garden turns"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "- If they're being "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "too",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "italic"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " careful: a low branch bends down and "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "offers fruit",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "bold"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " to whoever's closest"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The Close"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "cue",
          "kind": "music",
          "ref": "close",
          "label": "▶ close"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The trees are moving. Not swaying — "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "walking",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "italic"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ", dragging their roots out of the soil in long wet handfuls, closing the gaps between their trunks. The flowers turn to face you the way a crowd turns. Behind you, where the archway was, three trunks have already leaned together, and the vines are lacing them shut like fingers."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "And the whole garden takes one slow, wet, enormous breath."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Closing perimeter mechanics:",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "bold"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "- Each round the wall of growth advances — the open floor shrinks - Ground inside becomes difficult terrain as roots surface - End your turn touching the wall → grabbed: "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "restrained, and pulled",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "bold"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " - The real question: "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "can they reach the archway before it seals?",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "bold"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " Escape is a legitimate win; killing it is optional."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "📖 "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Stat block: 'The Garden of Eekso'",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "bold"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " — full block below under Fight (also 🏠 in the compendium)."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Fight"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "cue",
          "kind": "music",
          "ref": "fight",
          "label": "▶ fight"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            { "type": "text", "text": "THE GARDEN OF EEKSO — Gargantuan plant, CR 7", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }] }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            { "type": "text", "text": "AC 14 · HP 150 · Speed 0 (attacks from any tree/root/vine in the grove) · Tremorsense 60 ft, blind beyond · Init −1" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            { "type": "text", "text": "STR 19 (+4) · DEX 8 (−1) · CON 14 (+2) · INT 3 · WIS 12 · CHA 10 · Saves Str +7, Con +5 · " },
            { "type": "text", "text": "Vulnerable fire & slashing", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }] },
            { "type": "text", "text": " · Immune: blinded, charmed, deafened, frightened, prone" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            { "type": "text", "text": "Multiattack. ", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }] },
            { "type": "text", "text": "Two Grasping Boughs. Grappling doesn't limit its attack count — no shortage of limbs." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            { "type": "text", "text": "Grasping Bough. ", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }] },
            { "type": "text", "text": "+7 to hit, reach 20 ft. 13 (2d8+4) bludgeoning; Large or smaller → grappled (escape DC 14). A single hit dealing 10+ slashing severs the bough and frees its target (damage still counts)." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            { "type": "text", "text": "Reel (bonus action). ", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }] },
            { "type": "text", "text": "Every grappled creature is pulled 15 ft toward the pool." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            { "type": "text", "text": "The Garden Closes. ", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }] },
            { "type": "text", "text": "Start of its turn: the wall advances 10 ft inward; inside is difficult terrain. End your turn within 5 ft of the wall → DC 14 Str save or grappled (DC 14) and pulled 10 ft poolward. The archway seals fully 3 rounds after the close begins — squeezing out costs 10 ft of movement." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            { "type": "text", "text": "Fire-Shy. ", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }] },
            { "type": "text", "text": "Any fire damage → the wall doesn't advance on its next turn, and grappled creatures have advantage to escape until the end of that turn." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            { "type": "text", "text": "The Pool Is the Stomach. ", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }] },
            { "type": "text", "text": "In the pool: restrained (escape DC 14 Athletics); start of the creature's turn → 18 (4d8) acid from the feeding spines. " },
            { "type": "text", "text": "0 HP in the pool = pulled under and dissolved.", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }] }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            { "type": "text", "text": "False Chorus. ", "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }] },
            { "type": "text", "text": "Below half HP the birdsong restarts, sped up and wrong: hearers DC 13 Wis save or disadvantage on their next attack roll." }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "- "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Vulnerable to fire AND slashing",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "bold"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " — a big cut severs a grappling bough outright - Grappled creatures get reeled toward the pool. "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The pool is the stomach",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "bold"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " — held under, spine damage + acid. "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "What hits 0 HP in there dissolves — no body, no Revivify.",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "bold"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "After"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "cue",
          "kind": "music",
          "ref": "after",
          "label": "▶ after"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "- If they escaped: the garden is a garden again. Still. Warm. The pool perfectly clear, waiting for the next travellers."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "- If they killed it: the pool clouds grey, sinks away, and leaves a bare basin of dead flesh. The whole garden sags where it stands — and you can see it now for what it always was: one thing, wearing a garden."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "- Either way, the birds do not come back."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Loot (approved)",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "bold"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " — in the root-mass, takes a few minutes of digging: - "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "+1 Shield",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "bold"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " - "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Scroll of Revivify",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "bold"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " - ~60 gp in mixed old coin"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}